            <pdf>bratishchev4.pdf</pdf>
            <abstract>Let an autonomous n-th order system of differential equations
                have an invariant set. For an equilibrium point
                being on this set, we form the Jacobi matrix in this point and prove the
                formula for the factorization of the characteristic polynomial in two polynomials
                of lesser degrees. Such a factorization is useful in the problem of the
                design of controllers of dynamical systems. The proposed formula is applied
                to solve the known problem of controlling an inverted pendulum on a movable trolley.
                By using the method of analytical design of aggregated regulators
                we construct a single-level nonlinear control stabilizing the pendulum in
                vertical position for sufficiently large initial deviations.</abstract>
            <title>Factorization of the Characteristic Polynomial for the Equilibrium State of an Аutonomous System Having an Invariant Set</title>
